<!-- About the Game -->
<section class="about-section about-game reveal" id="about">
  <h2>About the Game</h2>
  <p>
    Speedy Bird started as a vanilla HTML5 Canvas recreation of the classic Flappy Bird.
    The twist: every pipe you clear, the game speeds up — pushing your reflexes to their
    limit. It was later ported to the Lynx cross-platform framework as a showcase of
    ReactLynx's capability to deliver native game-like experiences.
  </p>

  <!-- Speed meter -->
  <div class="speed-meter reveal" id="speedMeter">
    <div class="speed-fill"></div>
    <div class="speed-labels">
      <span>1.00&times; Normal</span>
      <span>1.73&times; Max Speed</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Medals -->
  <div class="medals-row reveal">
    <div class="medal medal-bronze">Bronze<br><small>10 pts</small></div>
    <div class="medal medal-silver">Silver<br><small>20 pts</small></div>
    <div class="medal medal-gold">Gold<br><small>30 pts</small></div>
    <div class="medal medal-platinum">Platinum<br><small>40 pts</small></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Game feature cards -->
  <div class="feature-grid reveal">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Physics</h3>
      <p>Gravity, velocity, and collision detection tuned for tight, fair gameplay — the same feel as the original, but with a speed twist.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Tile-Based Pipes</h3>
      <p>Pipes are assembled from sprite tiles, faithfully recreating the pixel art aesthetic of the original Flappy Bird.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Parallax</h3>
      <p>Background, ground, and pipes scroll at different speeds to create depth — the faster the bird, the more intense the parallax.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Medal System</h3>
      <p>Earn Bronze, Silver, Gold, or Platinum medals based on your score. Can you reach Platinum before the speed kills you?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Cross-Platform</h3>
      <p>Play in your browser via GitHub Pages, or run natively on iOS and Android through the Lynx framework build.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Pixel Perfect</h3>
      <p>Original sprites from the Spriters Resource, scaled 2&times; for retina displays. Sound effects included.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- About Lynx -->
<section class="about-section about-lynx reveal">
  <h2>About Lynx</h2>
  <p>
    Lynx is ByteDance's open-source cross-platform framework that powers apps used by
    hundreds of millions of people. ReactLynx brings familiar React patterns to native
    rendering — this project demonstrates it works just as well for games.
  </p>

  <div class="feature-grid reveal">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>ReactLynx</h3>
      <p>Write components using React syntax and lifecycle. The same mental model, targeting native Lynx rendering instead of the DOM.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Native Rendering</h3>
      <p>Lynx bypasses WebView for a native rendering engine, delivering smoother animations and lower latency on mobile devices.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>CSS Styling</h3>
      <p>Style components with a CSS subset that compiles to native layout primitives — no custom DSL to learn.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Rspack Toolchain</h3>
      <p>Fast Rust-based bundler (Rspack) powers the build pipeline, delivering near-instant hot-reload during development.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>6 Platforms</h3>
      <p>iOS, Android, Web, desktop, and more — a single ReactLynx codebase runs everywhere Lynx supports.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Battle-Tested</h3>
      <p>Used in production by ByteDance apps with hundreds of millions of monthly active users. This isn't an experiment — it's proven.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Quick Start -->
<section class="about-section about-project reveal">
  <h2>Quick Start</h2>
  <p>Clone the repo and run locally in minutes.</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <pre><code><span class="comment"># Clone the repository</span>
<span class="command">git clone</span> <span class="arg">https://github.com/jonathanperis/speedy-bird-lynx</span>

<span class="comment"># Navigate into the directory</span>
<span class="command">cd</span> <span class="arg">speedy-bird-lynx</span>

<span class="comment"># Install dependencies and run</span>
<span class="command">npm install</span>
<span class="command">npm run dev</span></code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

